The uneasy rift between White House adviser Kellyanne Conway and her husband, the indefatigable Trump critic George Conway, appeared to widen this weekend, when Kellyanne was forced to address their difference of opinion on the record.
Kellyanne, who steered Trump’s campaign, became infamous early on for her ardent and recursive defenses, characterized by reality-bending personal attacks on those who dared question the president.
Meanwhile George, a lawyer, has become a full-time Trump critic.
“Consider them as a product of his pathologies, and they make perfect sense.”This weekend’s split-screen extended to other topics.
Their marriage survives, the article posits, by the grace of a 15,000-square-foot house, where each can get some distance from the other.